  <div id="text-content_F68D6B30-18AE-0135-550F-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>You can access Canvas through an institution-specific Canvas URL, your school's website, a <a href="/t5/Student-Guide/How-do-I-accept-an-email-invitation-to-join-a-Canvas-course-as-a/ta-p/1563" target="_blank">course invitation email</a>, or the <a href="/t5/Canvas-Student-iOS-Guide/How-do-I-log-in-to-the-Student-app-on-my-iOS-device-with-a/ta-p/1940" target="_blank">Canvas Student iOS app</a> or <a href="/t5/Canvas-Student-Android-Guide/How-do-I-log-in-to-the-Student-app-on-my-Android-device-with-a/ta-p/1859" target="_blank">Canvas Student Android app</a>. </p>
<p>You must have an account to log in to Canvas. <a href="/t5/Troubleshooting/Logging-into-Canvas/ta-p/875" target="_blank">View troubleshooting steps if you are unable to log in to Canvas.</a></p>
<p><strong>Notes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>If you are associated with an institution using Canvas and do not know your username and password, please contact your site administrator.</li>
<li>If you are given a join code or a secret URL to join a course, learn how to <a href="/t5/Student-Guide/How-do-I-sign-up-for-a-Canvas-account-with-a-join-code-or-secret/ta-p/437" target="_blank">create a Canvas account</a>. </li>
<li>Learn more about navigating Canvas as a student in the <a href="https://community.canvaslms.com/t5/Student-Guide/tkb-p/student#GlobalNavigation" target="_blank">Canvas Student Global Navigation guides </a>or the <a href="https://community.canvaslms.com/t5/Video-Guide/tkb-p/videos#student-videos" target="_blank">Canvas Student Video guides</a>. </li>
</ul>
  </div>
</div>

